  <brief_title>Effect of Rituximab on Immunological Recall Response to Specific Antigens in the Treatment of Non-Hodgkin's Lymphoma</brief_title>
  <official_title>A Multicenter Study to Evaluate the Effect of Rituximab (IDEC-102) on Primary Humoral Response, Recall Response, and Maintenance of Acquired Immunity to Specific Antigens</official_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Biogen</agency>
      <agency_class>Industry</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Biogen</source>
  <oversight_info>
    <has_dmc>No</has_dmc>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to provide treatment for patients who have relapsed
      Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma (NHL) or refractory NHL, and to test the immunity of study subjects
      after receiving four treatments with rituximab.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
